subject: p15144601
Findings: Transvenous right atrial and right ventricular pacer leads appear in standard placement. Cardiomediastinal silhouette remains mildly enlarged but stable. The aorta appears somewhat tortuous with atherosclerotic calcifications. The lungs are clear with no evidence of consolidation, effusion, or pneumothorax. Median sternotomy wires appear aligned and intact. No acute fractures are identified. Mild bilateral acromio-clavicular degenerative changes are noted.
Impression: No acute cardiopulmonary process. Stable mild cardiomegaly.
